<?xml-model ../out/tls1.rnc application/relax-ng-compact-syntax?><div xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:mods="http://www.loc.gov/mods/v3" xmlns:tls="http://tls.kanripo.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" type="concept" xml:id="uuid-95e2fb89-8db5-4fd7-bb2e-7150f4825560"><head>EXORCISE</head><list type="altnames"><item>DRIVE OUT</item><item>CAST OUT</item><item>EXPEL</item><item>PURIFY</item><item>CLEANSE</item><item>PURGE</item></list><list type="translations"><item xml:lang="zh">去邪氣</item><item xml:lang="och">禊</item></list><div type="definition"><p>PRAY so as to TRY to REMOVE WICKED SUPERNATURAL FORCES.</p></div><div type="notes"><div type="old-chinese-criteria"><p>1. The most common word for exorcism is fú 祓, and the word refers specifically to shamanistic incantations designed to remove evil spirits, the shamans often being women.</p><p>2. The rarer ráng 禳 which is current in ZUO, does not specify any particular method of exorcism.</p><p>3. The fairly common xì 禊 refers specifically to the ritual exorcistic bath.</p><p>4. Jué 爝 refers to exorcism by the use of a burning torch.</p></div><div type="huang-jingui"><p>HUANG JINGUI 2006</p><p>SACRIFICE 11.</p><p>禳，卻變異之祭，泛指除邪消災之祭。</p><p>禬，除災害之祭。</p><p>祓，除災祭，強調除災之徹底性。</p><p>禜，禳除自然災害之祭。</p><p>祖，出行時祭祀路神，使不為阻，可特指設奠祭送死者。</p><p>禓，道路上對無主之鬼的祭祀，亦指逐強鬼之祭。</p><p>禊，於水濱洗濯、設祭以祓除不祥。</p><p>禦，祭祀以求免災，僅用於卜辭。</p><p>攻，攻擊驅逐災害之祭。</p><p>說，宣讀災害罪狀之祭。</p></div><div type="modern-chinese-criteria"><p>去邪氣 is a colloquial word referring to removing evil influences through exorcism.</p><p>軀鬼 focusses on the exorcising of ghosts.</p><p>rough draft to BEGIN TO identify synonym group members for analysis, based on CL etc. 18.11.2003. CH ／</p></div></div><div type="pointers"/><div type="source-references"><listBibl><bibl><ref target="#uuid-4acb4e0c-daab-4369-9991-912c64da1ee6">RITTER 1971-2007</ref><title>Historisches Woerterbuch der Philosophie</title><biblScope unit="page">2.6</biblScope><note><p>DAEMONOLOGIE</p></note></bibl><bibl><ref target="#uuid-65cb3fa8-ba3e-4eef-b23e-5b43a8bb8651">JONES 2005</ref><title>Encyclopedia of Religion</title><note><p>EXORCISM, PURIFICATION: AN OVERVIEW</p></note></bibl></listBibl></div><div type="words"><entry type="word" xml:id="uuid-24f093f8-3ffc-4c4c-8abf-5a3c315f98e0"><form corresp="#uuid-52abf88a-ca36-4df2-b088-97cb49590019"><orth>儺</orth><pron xml:lang="zh-Latn-x-pinyin">nuó</pron><pron xml:lang="zh-x-oc">mɢlaal</pron><pron xml:lang="zh-x-mc">nɑ</pron></form><sense xml:id="uuid-1f1304ca-942b-40b0-8b45-50eed2db2e3b"><gramGrp><pos>V</pos><tls:syn-func corresp="#uuid-c20780b3-41f9-491b-bb61-a269c1c4b48f">vi</tls:syn-func><usg type="warring-states-currency">3</usg></gramGrp><def>engage in exorcism</def></sense><sense xml:id="uuid-146ab4de-d211-4db3-be7b-5b64038a64e5"><gramGrp><pos>V</pos><tls:syn-func corresp="#uuid-fbfb2371-2537-4a99-a876-41b15ec2463c">vtoN</tls:syn-func><usg type="warring-states-currency">2</usg></gramGrp><def>exorcise</def></sense></entry><entry type="word" xml:id="uuid-5c087c6e-4245-45a6-9ee4-6983b00b313f"><form corresp="#uuid-30f7e02c-58dc-48bf-83fa-e0561a6ca7d3"><orth>爝</orth><pron xml:lang="zh-Latn-x-pinyin">jué</pron><pron xml:lang="zh-x-oc">tsewɡ</pron><pron xml:lang="zh-x-mc">tsi̯ɐk</pron></form><sense xml:id="uuid-2b950394-764a-4c7c-a7b5-b4b8a3b5cdc5"><gramGrp><pos>V</pos><tls:syn-func corresp="#uuid-c20780b3-41f9-491b-bb61-a269c1c4b48f">vi</tls:syn-func><tls:sem-feat corresp="#uuid-f55cff2f-f0e3-4f08-a89c-5d08fcf3fe89">act</tls:sem-feat><usg type="warring-states-currency">2</usg></gramGrp><def>exorcise evil by burning torches made of reed</def></sense></entry><entry type="word" xml:id="uuid-2fd315ca-15ab-47f5-b8b7-3c2228b6837a"><form corresp="#uuid-5d978f1a-f6d8-4f52-8985-76fca89cf8b7"><orth>祓</orth><pron xml:lang="zh-Latn-x-pinyin">fú</pron><pron xml:lang="zh-x-oc">phɯd</pron><pron xml:lang="zh-x-mc">phi̯ut</pron></form><sense xml:id="uuid-ce746dd5-b26a-4302-9f13-f64f279741a5"><gramGrp><pos>V</pos><tls:syn-func corresp="#uuid-a7e8eabf-866e-42db-88f2-b8f753ab74be">v[adN]</tls:syn-func><usg type="warring-states-currency">2</usg></gramGrp><def>exorciser</def></sense><sense xml:id="uuid-2a708478-c23f-419d-ac9e-a6437629418c"><gramGrp><pos>V</pos><tls:syn-func corresp="#uuid-fbfb2371-2537-4a99-a876-41b15ec2463c">vtoN</tls:syn-func><usg type="warring-states-currency">3</usg></gramGrp><def>conduct shamanistic incantations to remove evil influences from a person; exorcise</def></sense><sense xml:id="uuid-5dc23f3c-4b76-4a52-a55a-f9382ed500a0"><gramGrp><pos>V</pos><tls:syn-func corresp="#uuid-fbfb2371-2537-4a99-a876-41b15ec2463c">vtoN</tls:syn-func><tls:sem-feat corresp="#uuid-988c2bcf-3cdd-4b9e-b8a4-615fe3f7f81e">passive</tls:sem-feat><usg type="warring-states-currency">3</usg></gramGrp><def>be exorcised, be kept spiritually clean</def></sense><sense xml:id="uuid-2269a846-f895-432c-b57c-82f67650f114"><gramGrp><pos>V</pos><tls:syn-func corresp="#uuid-fbfb2371-2537-4a99-a876-41b15ec2463c">vtoN</tls:syn-func><tls:sem-feat corresp="#uuid-92ae8363-92d9-4b96-80a4-b07bc6788113">reflexive.自</tls:sem-feat></gramGrp><def>exorcise (oneself)</def></sense></entry><entry type="word" xml:id="uuid-2663b6d8-2b07-4167-841a-d2b4a671c237"><form corresp="#uuid-bd19fecb-b007-4b0f-93d5-5b5065f73643"><orth>禊</orth><pron xml:lang="zh-Latn-x-pinyin">xì</pron><pron xml:lang="zh-x-oc">ɡees</pron><pron xml:lang="zh-x-mc">ɦei</pron></form><sense xml:id="uuid-0ff4dcac-8b85-4c07-b2ea-51515f0d17a5"><gramGrp><pos>N</pos><tls:syn-func corresp="#uuid-76be1df4-3d73-4e5f-bbc2-729542645bc8">nab</tls:syn-func><tls:sem-feat corresp="#uuid-f55cff2f-f0e3-4f08-a89c-5d08fcf3fe89">act</tls:sem-feat><usg type="warring-states-currency">3</usg></gramGrp><def>ritual bath in a river as part of exorcism, washing away the evil spirit</def></sense><sense xml:id="uuid-f134e15d-165c-49ee-8c57-866d4f4c522f"><gramGrp><pos>V</pos><tls:syn-func corresp="#uuid-c20780b3-41f9-491b-bb61-a269c1c4b48f">vi</tls:syn-func><tls:sem-feat corresp="#uuid-f55cff2f-f0e3-4f08-a89c-5d08fcf3fe89">act</tls:sem-feat><usg type="warring-states-currency">4</usg></gramGrp><def>take a ritual bath in a river as part of exorcism, washing away the evil spirit</def></sense></entry><entry type="word" xml:id="uuid-c4df0c87-3a25-42fe-8d12-0b71eab1c87d"><form corresp="#uuid-ff7d482f-7154-46ed-8052-2c487fffc5d8"><orth>禜</orth><pron xml:lang="zh-Latn-x-pinyin">yíng</pron><pron xml:lang="zh-x-oc">ɢʷeŋ</pron><pron xml:lang="zh-x-mc">ɦɣaŋ</pron></form><sense xml:id="uuid-aa41c2a1-b905-4f84-9623-0071f66ac27e"><gramGrp><pos>V</pos><tls:syn-func corresp="#uuid-fbfb2371-2537-4a99-a876-41b15ec2463c">vtoN</tls:syn-func><usg type="warring-states-currency">2</usg></gramGrp><def>perform propitiatory or exorcistic sacrifices to spirits of mountains, rivers, stars, etc. in times of natural disasters (ZUO)</def></sense></entry><entry type="word" xml:id="uuid-921e18db-a64c-4ef1-992b-18e223a22bbd"><form corresp="#uuid-2c4ebcdc-82b9-40ac-afab-25db7644e9a1"><orth>禬</orth><pron xml:lang="zh-Latn-x-pinyin">guì</pron><pron xml:lang="zh-x-oc">kloobs</pron><pron xml:lang="zh-x-mc">kɑi</pron></form><sense xml:id="uuid-10136d30-4f6d-437e-b3c8-e392ee89d5b6"><gramGrp><pos>N</pos><tls:syn-func corresp="#uuid-8717712d-14a4-4ae2-be7a-6e18e61d929b">n</tls:syn-func><usg type="warring-states-currency">1</usg></gramGrp><def>sacrifice to avert calamities (ZHOULI)</def></sense></entry><entry type="word" xml:id="uuid-af59a119-bc6b-4478-b5fc-2ba225e6d71c"><form corresp="#uuid-009d48d2-e8bb-4644-9bc9-4cf3bd19925a"><orth>禳</orth><pron xml:lang="zh-Latn-x-pinyin">ráng</pron><pron xml:lang="zh-x-oc">njaŋ</pron><pron xml:lang="zh-x-mc">ȵi̯ɐŋ</pron></form><sense xml:id="uuid-2b38bc62-f676-48c1-87d4-c6a816353cdd"><gramGrp><pos>V</pos><tls:syn-func corresp="#uuid-c20780b3-41f9-491b-bb61-a269c1c4b48f">vi</tls:syn-func><usg type="warring-states-currency">2</usg></gramGrp><def>exorcise evil spirits through various practices</def></sense><sense xml:id="uuid-ff66866b-52a1-48b4-841b-875a973da6ec"><gr